            {# Accessibility #}
            <article class="card p-2">
                <div class="card-header">
                    <h2>üìå Accessibility</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p class="p-1">
                        For accessibility, set <code class="text-bold text-primary">aria-expanded</code> on the button only once to match the initial state.
                        After that, the script updates its value automatically when the dropdown opens or closes.
                    </p>

                    <p class="p-1">
                        Add <code class="text-bold text-primary">aria-controls</code> to link the button to the menu ID.
                        This helps assistive technologies understand which element is being toggled.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </article>

